parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause fires, loss of power, and stalling, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood latch can cause the hood to open while driving, obstructing the driver's view and potentially leading to accidents.
The failure of the door lock cylinder can cause the door to lock or unlock unexpectedly, potentially leaving the vehicle unsecured or trapping the occupants inside.
symptoms: The door lock cylinder comes out with the key
the door lock sticks or fails to open
the door lock falls out of the door handle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake line can cause the brakes to fail, potentially leading to accidents.

symptoms: Thick white steam or coolant coming out of the vents
boiling hot coolant pouring onto the feet
and hard braking due to hot fluid.
